he Old English form <i>Æþelbeorht</i>. The name is popular in a variety of forms in Western Europe, and has been traditional in a number of European princely families. It was out of favour in England for centuries, however, and the revival of its popularity in the 19th century was largely in honour of  Queen Victoria's  consort,  Prince Albert of Saxe-Coburg-Gotha ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Madog ap Adda was born in Ruabon, Denbighshire, Wales, United Kingdom as the son of Adda Llwyd ap Adda and Mali ferch Madog. He had at least 2 sons with Gwen ferch Llywelyn."},"et":{"–":"Surnud","–Male":"Surnud","–Female":"Surnud","1260–Male":"1260–Surnud","1287–Male":"1287–Surnud","1326–Male":"1326–Surnud","1330–Female":"1330–Surnud","about 1260":"umbes 1260","1326":"1326","ABT    1287":"umbes 1287","1287":"1287","1330":"1330","1260":"1260","Wales":"Wales","of,Rhiwabon,Denbighshire,Wales":"Ruabon, Denbighshire, Wales, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"–":"Kuollut","–Male":"Kuollut","–Female":"Kuollut","1260–Male":"1260–Kuollut","1287–Male":"1287–Kuollut","1326–Male":"1326–Kuollut","1330–Female":"1330–Kuollut","about 1260":"noin 1260","1326":"1326","ABT    1287":"noin 1287","1287":"1287","1330":"1330","1260":"1260","Wales":"Wales","of,Rhiwabon,Denbighshire,Wales":"Ruabon, Denbighshire, Wales, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"–":"Décédé","–Male":"Décédé","–Female":"Décédée","1260–Male":"1260–Décédé","1287–Male":"1287–Décédé","1326–Male":"1326–Décédé","1330–Female":"1330–Décédée","about 1260":"environ 1260","1326":"1326","ABT    1287":"environ 1287","1287":"1287","1330":"1330","1260":"1260","Wales":"Galles","of,Rhiwabon,Denbighshire,Wales":"Ruabon, Denbighshire, Pays de Galles, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Madog ap Adda est né à Ruabon, Denbighshire, Pays de Galles, Royaume-Uni, fils de Adda Llwyd ap Adda et Mali ferch Madog. Il a eu au moins 2 fils avec Gwen ferch Llywelyn."},"de":{"–":"Verstorben","–Male":"Verstorben","–Female":"Verstorben","1260–Male":"1260–Verstorben","1287–Male":"1287–Verst